Exoplanets in the SWEEPS-11 system


SWEEPS-11 b

SWEEPS-11 b was discovered by the Hubble Space Telescope observatory, in 2006-10, using the transit method. Its semi-major axis is 0.03 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of SWEEPS-11 b is 3084.600 times the mass of Earth. The radius of SWEEPS-11 b is 12.666 that of Earth. At more than 50 Earth masses, SWEEPS-11 b is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.
